article.story: BOSTON -- — Malik Mack scored 18 points as Harvard beat Columbia 62-59 on Friday night. Mack also had six assists and three steals for the Crimson (11-7, 2/3 Ivy League). Chisom Okpara scored 13 points while going 5 of 12 and 3 of 7 from the free throw line, and added seven rebounds. Louis Lesmond was 4 of 8 shooting (3 for 6 from 3-point range) to finish with 11 points. Kenny Noland finished with 12 points for the Lions (10-8, 1-4). Zine Eddine Bedri added eight points and six rebounds for Columbia. Avery Brown also had eight points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
